*** Settings ***
Documentation    Datepicker / date-picker widget validations: search filtering
...              and selection-populates-field round-trip. All project-agnostic
...              — locators are arguments so any datepicker implementation can
...              be tested.
...              Generated by scripts/new_keyword.py for form_validation/datepicker.resource.
Library          Browser
Library          String
Resource         _helpers.resource


*** Keywords ***
Validate Datepicker Search Filters Options
    [Documentation]    Opens a datepicker / combobox panel by clicking
    ...                ``${trigger_locator}``, types ``${query}`` into
    ...                ``${search_locator}``, then asserts that every
    ...                **visible** option matching ``${option_locator}``
    ...                contains ``${expected_match_substring}`` (case-insensitive).
    ...
    ...                Arguments:
    ...                - ``trigger_locator``          — selector for the button/input that opens the panel.
    ...                - ``search_locator``           — selector for the search/filter input inside the panel.
    ...                - ``option_locator``           — selector matching every option row in the panel.
    ...                - ``query``                    — text to type into the search field.
    ...                - ``expected_match_substring`` — substring each visible option must contain.
    [Arguments]    ${trigger_locator}    ${search_locator}    ${option_locator}
    ...            ${query}    ${expected_match_substring}
    Click    ${trigger_locator}
    Fill Text    ${search_locator}    ${query}
    # Brief wait for the filter animation / re-render.
    Sleep    200ms
    ${options}=    Get Elements    ${option_locator}
    ${visible_count}=    Set Variable    ${0}
    FOR    ${opt}    IN    @{options}
        ${hidden}=    Run Keyword And Return Status
        ...    Wait For Elements State    ${opt}    hidden    timeout=200ms
        IF    not ${hidden}
            ${text}=    Get Text    ${opt}
            ${lower_text}=    Convert To Lower Case    ${text}
            ${lower_sub}=     Convert To Lower Case    ${expected_match_substring}
            Should Contain    ${lower_text}    ${lower_sub}
            ...    msg=Visible option '${text}' does not contain expected substring '${expected_match_substring}'.
            ${visible_count}=    Evaluate    int(${visible_count}) + 1
        END
    END
    Should Be True    int(${visible_count}) >= 1
    ...    msg=Search for '${query}' produced no visible options — expected at least one containing '${expected_match_substring}'.

Validate Datepicker Selection Populates Field
    [Documentation]    Opens the datepicker panel via ``${trigger_locator}``,
    ...                clicks the first visible option matching
    ...                ``${option_locator}``, then asserts that
    ...                ``${field_locator}`` changed from its initial value and
    ...                now equals the option's visible text.
    ...
    ...                Arguments:
    ...                - ``trigger_locator`` — selector for the open-panel trigger.
    ...                - ``field_locator``   — selector for the readonly/text input that receives the value.
    ...                - ``option_locator``  — selector matching the option(s) to click.
    [Arguments]    ${trigger_locator}    ${field_locator}    ${option_locator}
    ${initial_value}=    Read Field Value    ${field_locator}
    Click    ${trigger_locator}
    ${options}=    Get Elements    ${option_locator}
    ${option_text}=    Get Text    ${options}[0]
    Click    ${options}[0]
    ${new_value}=    Read Field Value    ${field_locator}
    Should Not Be Equal    ${new_value}    ${initial_value}
    ...    msg=Field value did not change after clicking option '${option_text}'.
    ${option_text_trimmed}=    Strip String    ${option_text}
    Should Be Equal    ${new_value}    ${option_text_trimmed}
    ...    msg=Field value '${new_value}' does not match option text '${option_text_trimmed}'.
